    <p class="log">Every investigation begins with understanding the environment where the crime occurred.</p>

    <p>In this case, the human body is the environment — a massive, tightly coordinated city of over 37 trillion cells. Most members of this community live short, predictable lives. They perform their tasks, divide a few times, and eventually retire through programmed cell death.</p>

    <div class="alert-box"><p>NOT ALL CELLS OBEY THE LAW.</p></div>

    <p>Stem cells operate under their own set of rules. They are the body's permanent repair and maintenance crew, responsible for maintaining organs that constantly experience wear and tear. The intestinal epithelium is replaced approximately every four to five days through the activity of intestinal stem cells. Haematopoietic stem cells in bone marrow continually generate new blood cells to maintain circulation. Without these regenerative populations, tissues would quickly deteriorate and fail (Clevers, 2011).</p>

