    <p>This is where the investigation takes an unexpected turn. The cell responsible for maintaining tissues and keeping the body alive may also provide the conditions under which cancer can emerge. The stem cell — once seen as the body's maintenance worker — now begins to look like a key suspect in the case.</p>

    <div class="terminal-log">
      <div class="prompt">>> DET.MARK // INTERROGATION LOG</div>
      <p>If stem cells are so important for survival, why has evolution not eliminated the mechanism that causes cancer to develop?</p>
